---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const articleHtml = `<h3>How do I update my data from QuickBooks?</h3>
<p>Most of the data is updated automatically shortly after it has been saved in QuickBooks Online.</p>
<p>You can also manually update data from QuickBooks by clicking on the Refresh data link above the Invoices table or in the QuickBooks section of the Settings page:</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-refresh-data.png" alt="Refresh data from QuickBooks" width="1200" height="500" loading="lazy"></p>

<h3>How do I disconnect from QuickBooks?</h3>
<p>You can disconnect HedgeFlows from your QuickBooks account in the QuickBooks section of our Settings page:</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-disconnect.png" alt="Disconnect QuickBooks from Settings" width="1200" height="500" loading="lazy"></p>

<h3>Why can't I see my paid invoices?</h3>
<p>By default, we filter out paid and voided invoices from the Invoice table. You can include them in the table by clicking "All" in the top section of the table:</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-paid-invoices.png" alt="Show all invoices including paid" width="1200" height="500" loading="lazy"></p>

<h3>Can you process bulk payments and write them back to QuickBooks?</h3>
<p>Yes, we support bulk payments and aggregating invoices to the same beneficiary via our Bulk payments flow. Simply choose the invoices you want to pay from the Invoices table. We will process them in bulk and record individual currency payments with correct exchange rates and currency amounts back to QuickBooks:</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-bulk-payments.png" alt="Bulk payments for QuickBooks invoices" width="1200" height="500" loading="lazy"></p>

<h3>Which version of QuickBooks does HedgeFlows support?</h3>
<p>HedgeFlows integrates with <strong>QuickBooks Online</strong>. The desktop version of QuickBooks is not currently supported. If you are using QuickBooks Desktop and would like to discuss integration options, please <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.</p>

<h3>What doesn't your integration do?</h3>
<p>We currently don't offer the following:</p>
<ol>
<li>Importing sales and purchase orders (coming soon)</li>
<li>Updating details for saved Contacts using data from QuickBooks. If you want to import updated contact details into HedgeFlows you need to set up a new contact in our system.</li>
<li>Importing invoices, bills etc. in home currency (coming soon)</li>
<li>Automatically recording bank transfers from your bank to HedgeFlows for you in QuickBooks (coming soon).</li>
<li>Recording Collections and Conversion transactions (coming soon).</li>
</ol>
<p>If you can't find the feature that you would like to see, please <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.</p>

<h3>Where in QuickBooks should I see payments done via HedgeFlows?</h3>
<p>Provided you have permitted us to do so during QuickBooks integration setup, we will automatically record foreign currency payments executed from your HedgeFlows account in QuickBooks. Regular currency transfers are recorded in a HedgeFlows Clearing Account. You will need to add a funding transfer from your bank account to the HedgeFlows account manually.</p>

<h3>How do payment processing fees appear in QuickBooks?</h3>
<p>Payment processing fees will appear on the HedgeFlows Clearing account.</p>`;
---

<PageLayout
  title="QuickBooks integration - FAQs | Help Centre | HedgeFlows"
  description="Frequently asked questions about the HedgeFlows and QuickBooks Online integration — data updates, disconnecting, bulk payments and more."
>
  <section class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-text-muted mb-8">
        <a href="/help" class="hover:text-brand-green transition-colors">Help Centre</a>
        <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m8.25 4.5 7.5 7.5-7.5 7.5" />
        </svg>
        <a href="/help/#integrations" class="hover:text-brand-green transition-colors">Integrations</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-[1.75rem] md:text-[2.25rem] font-bold text-text-heading leading-tight mb-8">QuickBooks integration - FAQs</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray max-w-none
                  [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-bold [&_h2]:text-text-heading [&_h2]:mt-10 [&_h2]:mb-4
                  [&_h3]:text-xl [&_h3]:font-semibold [&_h3]:text-text-heading [&_h3]:mt-8 [&_h3]:mb-3
                  [&_h4]:text-lg [&_h4]:font-semibold [&_h4]:text-text-heading [&_h4]:mt-6 [&_h4]:mb-2
                  [&_p]:text-text-body [&_p]:leading-relaxed [&_p]:mb-4
                  [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:pl-6 [&_ul]:mb-4 [&_ul_li]:text-text-body [&_ul_li]:mb-2
                  [&_ol]:list-decimal [&_ol]:pl-6 [&_ol]:mb-4 [&_ol_li]:text-text-body [&_ol_li]:mb-2
                  [&_a]:text-brand-green [&_a]:underline
                  [&_table]:w-full [&_table]:border-collapse [&_table]:mb-6
                  [&_th]:bg-gray-50 [&_th]:px-4 [&_th]:py-2.5 [&_th]:text-left [&_th]:text-sm [&_th]:font-semibold [&_th]:text-text-heading [&_th]:border [&_th]:border-gray-200
                  [&_td]:px-4 [&_td]:py-2.5 [&_td]:text-sm [&_td]:text-text-body [&_td]:border [&_td]:border-gray-200
                  [&_img]:rounded-xl [&_img]:shadow-sm [&_img]:my-6
                  [&_iframe]:rounded-xl [&_iframe]:my-6 [&_iframe]:w-full [&_iframe]:aspect-video">
        <Fragment set:html={articleHtml} />
      </div>

      <!-- Back link -->
      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
        <a href="/help" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[0.9375rem] text-brand-green font-medium hover:underline">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.5 19.5 3 12m0 0 7.5-7.5M3 12h18" />
          </svg>
          Back to Help Centre
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
